{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775867838986,"sessionID":"ses_28607dc6fffe0RHK34NP7uECaP","part":{"id":"prt_d79f8c1e5001V05Yc65iHwkqYM","messageID":"msg_d79f89bcc001MFlVW4YVbo9P0I","sessionID":"ses_28607dc6fffe0RHK34NP7uECaP","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-a47ae6ccc55a447e8474de64361e08bb","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-022/spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-022/spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # CLI publish 命令 Specification\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: [To be filled during spec definition]\n5: \n6: ## Requirements\n7: [To be filled during spec definition]\n\n(End of file - total 7 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# CLI publish 命令 Specification\n\n## Purpose\n[To be filled during spec definition]\n\n## Requirements\n[To be filled during spec definition]","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-022/spec.md","time":{"start":1775867838977,"end":1775867838985}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775867838989,"sessionID":"ses_28607dc6fffe0RHK34NP7uECaP","part":{"id":"prt_d79f8bc74001eF2tL0CkY6BEib","messageID":"msg_d79f89bcc001MFlVW4YVbo9P0I","sessionID":"ses_28607dc6fffe0RHK34NP7uECaP","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-9dc0a0ff19b94a2f8028ecbab0f83b7f","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-022/design.md","limit":200},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-022/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-022: CLI publish 命令 Design Document\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: This design document describes the implementation of the `publish` command for the AgentCube CLI toolkit. The publish command is responsible for deploying packaged agent workloads to either the AgentCube platform (using AgentRuntime custom resources) or standard Kubernetes (using Deployment and Service resources), including container image management and registry integration.\n6: \n7: ## Background\n8: \n9: The AgentCube CLI toolkit provides a comprehensive command-line interface for managing AI agent lifecycles. The publish command is a critical component that enables developers to deploy their agents to production environments. It supports two deployment targets:\n10: \n11: 1. **AgentCube Provider**: Deploys agents using the AgentRuntime custom resource for enhanced features like session management and workload orchestration\n12: 2. **Kubernetes Provider**: Deploys agents using standard Kubernetes Deployment and NodePort Service resources for broader compatibility\n13: \n14: The publish command must handle various scenarios including:\n15: - Local image building and pushing to registries\n16: - Cloud-based image building\n17: - Image URL specification for pre-built images\n18: - Registry authentication\n19: - Version management\n20: - Deployment configuration (replicas, node ports, namespaces)\n21: - Provider-specific deployment strategies\n22: \n23: ## Architecture\n24: \n25: ### Component Overview\n26: \n27: ```\n28: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n29: │                      CLI publish Command                        │\n30: │                                                                  │\n31: │  ┌──────────────────┐  ┌──────────────────┐  ┌─────────────────┐│\n32: │  │ PublishRuntime   │  │  DockerService   │  │ MetadataService ││\n33: │  │                  │  │                  │  │                 ││\n34: │  │ • publish()      │  │ • push_image()   │  │ • load_metadata ││\n35: │  │ • _publish_cr()  │  │ • login()        │  │ • save_metadata ││\n36: │  │ • _publish_k8s() │  │ • tag_image()    │  │ • validate()    ││\n37: │  └────────┬─────────┘  └────────┬─────────┘  └────────┬────────┘│\n38: │           │                     │                     │          │\n39: │           ▼                     ▼                     ▼          │\n40: │  ┌────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐ │\n41: │  │                Provider Layer                              │ │\n42: │  │  ┌──────────────────┐  ┌──────────────────┐              │ │\n43: │  │  │ AgentCubeProvider│  │ KubernetesProvider│              │ │\n44: │  │  │                  │  │                  │              │ │\n45: │  │  │ • deploy_agent_  │  │ • deploy_agent() │              │ │\n46: │  │  │   runtime()      │  │ • wait_for_      │              │ │\n47: │  │  │ • get_agent_     │  │   ready()        │              │ │\n48: │  │  │   runtime()      │  │ • delete_agent() │              │ │\n49: │  │  └──────────────────┘  └──────────────────┘              │ │\n50: │  └────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘ │\n51: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n52:                             │\n53:                             ▼\n54: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n55: │                      Target Platform                             │\n56: │                                                                  │\n57: │  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │\n58: │  │                Kubernetes Cluster                         │  │\n59: │  │  • AgentRuntime CRD (AgentCube provider)                  │  │\n60: │  │  • Deployment/Service (Kubernetes provider)               │  │\n61: │  │  • Pods with agent containers                             │  │\n62: │  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  │\n63: │                                                                  │\n64: │  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │\n65: │  │                Container Registry                         │  │\n66: │  │  • Docker Hub / Harbor / GCR / ACR                        │  │\n67: │  │  • Authentication and authorization                       │  │\n68: │  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  │\n69: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n70: ```\n71: \n72: ### Command Flow\n73: \n74: ```\n75: publish(workspace, version, image_url, provider, ...options)\n76: │\n77: ├─→ Load metadata from workspace\n78: │   └─→ Validate metadata and prerequisites\n79: │\n80: ├─→ Prepare image for publishing\n81: │   ├─→ Local build mode:\n82: │   │   ├─→ Validate Docker availability\n83: │   │   ├─→ Build image (if needed)\n84: │   │   ├─→ Tag image with registry URL\n85: │   │   └─→ Push to registry with authentication\n86: │   │\n87: │   └─→ Cloud build mode:\n88: │       ├─→ Call cloud provider API\n89: │       └─→ Use returned image URL\n90: │\n91: ├─→ Deploy based on provider\n92: │   ├─→ agentcube provider:\n93: │   │   ├─→ Validate router_url and workload_manager_url\n94: │   │   ├─→ Create AgentRuntime CR\n95: │   │   ├─→ Set session timeout (15m, 8h max)\n96: │   │   └─→ Return agent_id and endpoint\n97: │   │\n98: │   └─→ k8s provider:\n99: │       ├─→ Create Deployment\n100: │       ├─→ Create NodePort Service\n101: │       ├─→ Wait for rollout (120s timeout)\n102: │       ├─→ Get status and endpoints\n103: │       └─→ Handle readiness failures\n104: │\n105: ├─→ Update metadata with deployment info\n106: │   └─→ Save agent_metadata.yaml\n107: │\n108: └─→ Display results to user\n109:     └─→ Show deployment URL, agent_id, status\n110: ```\n111: \n112: ## Implementation Details\n113: \n114: ### 1. Typer Command Interface\n115: \n116: **File**: `agentcube/cli/main.py`\n117: \n118: **Purpose**: Define the publish command interface with all required options.\n119: \n120: **Implementation**:\n121: \n122: ```python\n123: @app.command()\n124: def publish(\n125:     workspace: str = typer.Option(\n126:         \".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\",\n127:         help=\"Path to the agent workspace directory\",\n128:         show_default=True,\n129:     ),\n130:     version: Optional[str] = typer.Option(\n131:         None, \"--version\",\n132:         help=\"Semantic version string (e.g., v1.0.0)\",\n133:     ),\n134:     image_url: Optional[str] = typer.Option(\n135:         None, \"--image-url\",\n136:         help=\"Image repository URL (required in local build mode)\",\n137:     ),\n138:     image_username: Optional[str] = typer.Option(\n139:         None, \"--image-username\",\n140:         help=\"Username for image repository\",\n141:     ),\n142:     image_password: Optional[str] = typer.Option(\n143:         None, \"--image-password\",\n144:         help=\"Password for image repository\",\n145:     ),\n146:     description: Optional[str] = typer.Option(\n147:         None, \"--description\",\n148:         help=\"Agent description\",\n149:     ),\n150:     region: Optional[str] = typer.Option(\n151:         None, \"--region\",\n152:         help=\"Deployment region\",\n153:     ),\n154:     cloud_provider: Optional[str] = typer.Option(\n155:         None, \"--cloud-provider\",\n156:         help=\"Cloud provider name (e.g., huawei)\",\n157:     ),\n158:     provider: str = typer.Option(\n159:         \"agentcube\", \"--provider\",\n160:         help=\"Target provider: 'agentcube' (AgentRuntime CR) or 'k8s' (Deployment/Service)\",\n161:     ),\n162:     node_port: Optional[int] = typer.Option(\n163:         None, \"--node-port\",\n164:         help=\"Specific NodePort to use (30000-32767) for K8s deployment\",\n165:     ),\n166:     replicas: Optional[int] = typer.Option(\n167:         None, \"--replicas\",\n168:         help=\"Number of replicas for K8s deployment (default: 1)\",\n169:     ),\n170:     namespace: Optional[str] = typer.Option(\n171:         None, \"--namespace\",\n172:         help=\"The namespace for the deployment\",\n173:     ),\n174:     verbose: bool = typer.Option(\n175:         False, \"--verbose\",\n176:         help=\"Enable detailed logging\",\n177:     ),\n178: ) -> None:\n179:     \"\"\"Publish and deploy an agent to AgentCube or Kubernetes.\"\"\"\n180:     try:\n181:         runtime = PublishRuntime(verbose=verbose, provider=provider)\n182: \n183:         with typer.progress(\n184:             tasks=[\n185:                 (\"Loading workspace metadata\", \"load_metadata\"),\n186:                 (\"Preparing image for publishing\", \"prepare_image\"),\n187:                 (\"Deploying agent\", \"deploy\"),\n188:                 (\"Updating metadata\", \"update_metadata\"),\n189:             ],\n190:         ) as progress:\n191:             metadata_path = runtime.publish(\n192:                 workspace_path=Path(workspace),\n193:                 version=version,\n194:                 image_url=image_url,\n195:                 image_username=image_username,\n196:                 image_password=image_password,\n197:                 description=description,\n198:                 region=region,\n199:                 cloud_provider=cloud_provider,\n200:                 provider=provider,\n\n(Showing lines 1-200 of 1657. Use offset=201 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-022: CLI publish 命令 Design Document\n\n## Overview\n\nThis design document describes the implementation of the `publish` command for the AgentCube CLI toolkit. The publish command is responsible for deploying packaged agent workloads to either the AgentCube platform (using AgentRuntime custom resources) or standard Kubernetes (using Deployment and Service resources), including container image management and registry integration.\n\n## Background\n\nThe AgentCube CLI toolkit provides a comprehensive command-line interface for managing AI agent lifecycles. The publish command is a critical component that enables developers to deploy their agents to production environments. It supports two deployment targets:\n\n1. **AgentCube Provider**: Deploys agents using the AgentRuntime custom resource for enhanced features like session management and workload orchestration\n2. **Kubernetes Provider**: Deploys agents using standard Kubernetes Deployment and NodePort Service resources for broader compatibility\n\nThe publish command must handle various scenarios including:\n- Local image building and pushing to registries\n- Cloud-based image building\n- Image URL specification for pre-built images\n- Registry authentication\n- Version management\n- Deployment configuration (replicas, node ports, namespaces)","truncated":true,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-022/design.md","time":{"start":1775867838974,"end":1775867838986}}}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1775867839013,"sessionID":"ses_28607dc6fffe0RHK34NP7uECaP","part":{"id":"prt_d79f8c20c001YBPeIQIT6b3AVf","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","messageID":"msg_d79f89bcc001MFlVW4YVbo9P0I","sessionID":"ses_28607dc6fffe0RHK34NP7uECaP","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":48558,"input":6319,"output":256,"reasoning":0,"cache":{"write":0,"read":41983}},"cost":0}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775867847740,"sessionID":"ses_28607dc6fffe0RHK34NP7uECaP","part":{"id":"prt_d79f8e438001h0k4ppHqBLWlGG","messageID":"msg_d79f8c234001pDHYfVvNJAyzw5","sessionID":"ses_28607dc6fffe0RHK34NP7uECaP","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775867850411,"sessionID":"ses_28607dc6fffe0RHK34NP7uECaP","part":{"id":"prt_d79f8ee840014qozBtke7zJUvV","messageID":"msg_d79f8c234001pDHYfVvNJAyzw5","sessionID":"ses_28607dc6fffe0RHK34NP7uECaP","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-590692d781bc40798824d390ff4e5d6a","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-022/design.md","limit":400,"offset":200},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-022/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n200:                 provider=provider,\n201:                 node_port=node_port,\n202:                 replicas=replicas,\n203:                 namespace=namespace,\n204:                 progress=progress,\n205:             )\n206: \n207:         console.print(\n208:             f\"[green]✓[/green] Agent published successfully\",\n209:             f\"  Metadata: {metadata_path}\",\n210:         )\n211: \n212:     except Exception as e:\n213:         _handle_error(e, \"publish\", verbose)\n214: ```\n215: \n216: **Key Features**:\n217: - Comprehensive option set for all publishing scenarios\n218: - Rich progress tracking with multiple tasks\n219: - Provider selection (agentcube/k8s)\n220: - Registry authentication support\n221: - Kubernetes deployment customization (node_port, replicas, namespace)\n222: - Error handling with verbose mode\n223: \n224: ### 2. PublishRuntime Class\n225: \n226: **File**: `agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py`\n227: \n228: **Purpose**: Core publish logic orchestrating image preparation and deployment.\n229: \n230: **Implementation**:\n231: \n232: ```python\n233: class PublishRuntime:\n234:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False, provider: str = \"agentcube\") -> None:\n235:         self.verbose = verbose\n236:         self.provider = provider\n237:         self.logger = get_logger(__name__, level=logging.DEBUG if verbose else logging.INFO)\n238:         self.metadata_service = MetadataService(verbose=verbose)\n239:         self.docker_service = DockerService(verbose=verbose)\n240: \n241:     def publish(\n242:         self,\n243:         workspace_path: Path,\n244:         **options: Any,\n245:     ) -> Path:\n246:         \"\"\"Publish an agent to the specified provider.\"\"\"\n247:         self.logger.info(f\"Publishing agent from {workspace_path}\")\n248: \n249:         # Load and validate metadata\n250:         metadata = self.metadata_service.load_metadata(workspace_path)\n251: \n252:         # Apply option overrides\n253:         if options.get(\"description\"):\n254:             metadata.description = options[\"description\"]\n255:         if options.get(\"version\"):\n256:             metadata.version = options[\"version\"]\n257:         if options.get(\"region\"):\n258:             metadata.region = options[\"region\"]\n259: \n260:         # Prepare image for publishing\n261:         image_url = self._prepare_image_for_publishing(\n262:             workspace_path,\n263:             metadata,\n264:             options,\n265:         )\n266: \n267:         # Deploy based on provider\n268:         if self.provider == \"agentcube\":\n269:             agent_info = self._publish_cr_to_k8s(\n270:                 workspace_path,\n271:                 metadata,\n272:                 image_url,\n273:                 **options,\n274:             )\n275:         else:\n276:             agent_info = self._publish_k8s(\n277:                 workspace_path,\n278:                 metadata,\n279:                 image_url,\n280:                 **options,\n281:             )\n282: \n283:         # Update metadata with deployment info\n284:         self._update_publish_metadata(workspace_path, agent_info)\n285: \n286:         return workspace_path / \"agent_metadata.yaml\"\n287: \n288:     def _prepare_image_for_publishing(\n289:         self,\n290:         workspace_path: Path,\n291:         metadata: AgentMetadata,\n292:         options: Dict[str, Any],\n293:     ) -> str:\n294:         \"\"\"Prepare and push image to registry.\"\"\"\n295:         if metadata.build_mode == \"local\":\n296:             return self._prepare_local_image(\n297:                 workspace_path,\n298:                 metadata,\n299:                 options,\n300:             )\n301:         else:\n302:             return self._prepare_cloud_image(\n303:                 workspace_path,\n304:                 metadata,\n305:                 options,\n306:             )\n307: \n308:     def _prepare_local_image(\n309:         self,\n310:         workspace_path: Path,\n311:         metadata: AgentMetadata,\n312:         options: Dict[str, Any],\n313:     ) -> str:\n314:         \"\"\"Prepare local image by pushing to registry.\"\"\"\n315:         # Validate Docker is available\n316:         if not self.docker_service.check_docker_available():\n317:             raise RuntimeError(\"Docker is not available or not running\")\n318: \n319:         # Get image URL from options or metadata\n320:         image_url = options.get(\"image_url\") or metadata.image_url\n321:         if not image_url:\n322:             raise ValueError(\n323:                 \"Image URL is required for local build mode. \"\n324:                 \"Use --image-url or set image_url in metadata.\"\n325:             )\n326: \n327:         # Build local image name\n328:         local_image_name = f\"{metadata.agent_name}:latest\"\n329: \n330:         # Tag image for registry\n331:         registry_url = options.get(\"registry_url\") or metadata.registry_url\n332:         registry_username = options.get(\"image_username\") or metadata.registry_username\n333:         registry_password = options.get(\"image_password\") or metadata.registry_password\n334: \n335:         self.logger.info(f\"Tagging image {local_image_name} -> {image_url}\")\n336:         self.docker_service._tag_image_sdk(local_image_name, image_url)\n337: \n338:         # Push to registry\n339:         self.logger.info(f\"Pushing image to registry: {image_url}\")\n340:         push_result = self.docker_service.push_image(\n341:             image_name=image_url,\n342:             registry_url=registry_url,\n343:             username=registry_username,\n344:             password=registry_password,\n345:         )\n346: \n347:         self.logger.info(f\"Image pushed successfully: {push_result['pushed_image']}\")\n348:         return push_result[\"pushed_image\"]\n349: \n350:     def _prepare_cloud_image(\n351:         self,\n352:         workspace_path: Path,\n353:         metadata: AgentMetadata,\n354:         options: Dict[str, Any],\n355:     ) -> str:\n356:         \"\"\"Prepare cloud image by calling cloud provider API.\"\"\"\n357:         cloud_provider = options.get(\"cloud_provider\") or metadata.cloud_provider\n358:         if not cloud_provider:\n359:             raise ValueError(\n360:                 \"Cloud provider is required for cloud build mode. \"\n361:                 \"Use --cloud-provider or set cloud_provider in metadata.\"\n362:             )\n363: \n364:         # Call cloud provider build API\n365:         self.logger.info(f\"Building image in cloud: {cloud_provider}\")\n366: \n367:         # Placeholder for cloud provider integration\n368:         # This would call the appropriate cloud provider API\n369:         # For now, raise NotImplementedError\n370:         raise NotImplementedError(\n371:             f\"Cloud build mode for provider '{cloud_provider}' is not yet implemented\"\n372:         )\n373: \n374:     def _publish_cr_to_k8s(\n375:         self,\n376:         workspace_path: Path,\n377:         metadata: AgentMetadata,\n378:         image_url: str,\n379:         **options: Any,\n380:     ) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n381:         \"\"\"Publish agent using AgentCube provider (AgentRuntime CR).\"\"\"\n382:         from agentcube.services.agentcube_provider import AgentCubeProvider\n383: \n384:         # Validate required fields\n385:         if not metadata.router_url:\n386:             raise ValueError(\n387:                 \"router_url is required for agentcube provider. \"\n388:                 \"Set it in agent_metadata.yaml.\"\n389:             )\n390:         if not metadata.workload_manager_url:\n391:             raise ValueError(\n392:                 \"workload_manager_url is required for agentcube provider. \"\n393:                 \"Set it in agent_metadata.yaml.\"\n394:             )\n395: \n396:         namespace = options.get(\"namespace\") or \"default\"\n397:         provider = AgentCubeProvider(\n398:             namespace=namespace,\n399:             verbose=self.verbose,\n400:         )\n401: \n402:         # Deploy AgentRuntime CR\n403:         self.logger.info(f\"Deploying AgentRuntime CR for {metadata.agent_name}\")\n404: \n405:         deploy_result = provider.deploy_agent_runtime(\n406:             agent_name=metadata.agent_name,\n407:             image_url=image_url,\n408:             port=metadata.port,\n409:             entrypoint=metadata.entrypoint,\n410:             env_vars={\n411:                 \"WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL\": metadata.workload_manager_url,\n412:                 \"ROUTER_URL\": metadata.router_url,\n413:             },\n414:             workload_manager_url=metadata.workload_manager_url,\n415:             router_url=metadata.router_url,\n416:             readiness_probe_path=metadata.readiness_probe_path or \"/health\",\n417:             readiness_probe_port=metadata.readiness_probe_port or metadata.port,\n418:         )\n419: \n420:         self.logger.info(f\"AgentRuntime CR deployed: {deploy_result}\")\n421: \n422:         return {\n423:             \"agent_id\": deploy_result.get(\"agent_id\"),\n424:             \"agent_endpoint\": deploy_result.get(\"agent_endpoint\"),\n425:             \"provider\": \"agentcube\",\n426:             \"namespace\": namespace,\n427:             \"image_url\": image_url,\n428:         }\n429: \n430:     def _publish_k8s(\n431:         self,\n432:         workspace_path: Path,\n433:         metadata: AgentMetadata,\n434:         image_url: str,\n435:         **options: Any,\n436:     ) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n437:         \"\"\"Publish agent using standard Kubernetes provider.\"\"\"\n438:         from agentcube.services.k8s_provider import KubernetesProvider\n439: \n440:         namespace = options.get(\"namespace\") or \"default\"\n441:         replicas = options.get(\"replicas\") or 1\n442:         node_port = options.get(\"node_port\")\n443: \n444:         provider = KubernetesProvider(\n445:             namespace=namespace,\n446:             verbose=self.verbose,\n447:         )\n448: \n449:         # Deploy using standard Kubernetes resources\n450:         self.logger.info(f\"Deploying agent {metadata.agent_name} to Kubernetes\")\n451: \n452:         deploy_result = provider.deploy_agent(\n453:             agent_name=metadata.agent_name,\n454:             image_url=image_url,\n455:             port=metadata.port,\n456:             entrypoint=metadata.entrypoint,\n457:             replicas=replicas,\n458:             node_port=node_port,\n459:             env_vars={\n460:                 \"PORT\": str(metadata.port),\n461:             },\n462:         )\n463: \n464:         self.logger.info(f\"Agent deployed: {deploy_result}\")\n465: \n466:         return {\n467:             \"deployment_name\": deploy_result[\"deployment_name\"],\n468:             \"service_name\": deploy_result[\"service_name\"],\n469:             \"namespace\": namespace,\n470:             \"service_url\": deploy_result[\"service_url\"],\n471:             \"provider\": \"k8s\",\n472:             \"replicas\": replicas,\n473:             \"node_port\": deploy_result.get(\"node_port\"),\n474:             \"image_url\": image_url,\n475:         }\n476: \n477:     def _update_publish_metadata(\n478:         self,\n479:         workspace_path: Path,\n480:         agent_info: Dict[str, Any],\n481:     ) -> None:\n482:         \"\"\"Update metadata with deployment information.\"\"\"\n483:         metadata = self.metadata_service.load_metadata(workspace_path)\n484: \n485:         # Update deployment-specific fields\n486:         if agent_info[\"provider\"] == \"agentcube\":\n487:             metadata.agent_id = agent_info[\"agent_id\"]\n488:             metadata.agent_endpoint = agent_info[\"agent_endpoint\"]\n489:         else:\n490:             metadata.k8s_deployment = {\n491:                 \"deployment_name\": agent_info[\"deployment_name\"],\n492:                 \"service_name\": agent_info[\"service_name\"],\n493:                 \"service_url\": agent_info[\"service_url\"],\n494:                 \"replicas\": agent_info[\"replicas\"],\n495:                 \"node_port\": agent_info.get(\"node_port\"),\n496:             }\n497: \n498:         # Update common fields\n499:         metadata.image_url = agent_info[\"image_url\"]\n500: \n501:         # Save updated metadata\n502:         self.metadata_service.save_metadata(workspace_path, metadata)\n503: \n504:         self.logger.info(f\"Updated metadata at {workspace_path}/agent_metadata.yaml\")\n505: ```\n506: \n507: **Key Features**:\n508: - Provider abstraction (agentcube/k8s)\n509: - Image preparation and registry push\n510: - CR deployment for AgentCube provider\n511: - Standard K8s deployment for k8s provider\n512: - Metadata updates with deployment info\n513: - Comprehensive error handling\n514: - Progress tracking support\n515: \n516: ### 3. DockerService Integration\n517: \n518: **File**: `agentcube/services/docker_service.py`\n519: \n520: **Purpose**: Handle Docker operations for image tagging and pushing.\n521: \n522: **Enhanced Methods**:\n523: \n524: ```python\n525: def _docker_login_sdk(self, registry: Optional[str], username: str, password: str) -> None:\n526:     \"\"\"Login to Docker registry using SDK.\"\"\"\n527:     client = docker.from_env()\n528:     try:\n529:         if registry:\n530:             client.login(username=username, password=password, registry=registry)\n531:         else:\n532:             client.login(username=username, password=password)\n533:         self.logger.info(f\"Successfully logged in to registry: {registry or 'Docker Hub'}\")\n534:     except Exception as e:\n535:         self.logger.error(f\"Failed to login to registry: {e}\")\n536:         raise\n537: \n538: def _tag_image_sdk(self, source_image: str, target_image: str) -> None:\n539:     \"\"\"Tag Docker image using SDK.\"\"\"\n540:     client = docker.from_env()\n541:     try:\n542:         image = client.images.get(source_image)\n543:         image.tag(target_image)\n544:         self.logger.info(f\"Tagged image: {source_image} -> {target_image}\")\n545:     except docker.errors.ImageNotFound:\n546:         self.logger.error(f\"Image not found: {source_image}\")\n547:         raise\n548:     except Exception as e:\n549:         self.logger.error(f\"Failed to tag image: {e}\")\n550:         raise\n551: ```\n552: \n553: **Key Features**:\n554: - Registry authentication\n555: - Image tagging for registry\n556: - Error handling and logging\n557: - SDK-based operations\n558: \n559: ### 4. AgentCubeProvider Integration\n560: \n561: **File**: `agentcube/services/agentcube_provider.py`\n562: \n563: **Purpose**: Deploy agents using AgentRuntime custom resources.\n564: \n565: **Enhanced Methods**:\n566: \n567: ```python\n568: def deploy_agent_runtime(\n569:     self,\n570:     agent_name: str,\n571:     image_url: str,\n572:     port: int,\n573:     entrypoint: Optional[str] = None,\n574:     env_vars: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None,\n575:     workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = None,\n576:     router_url: Optional[str] = None,\n577:     readiness_probe_path: Optional[str] = None,\n578:     readiness_probe_port: Optional[int] = None,\n579: ) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n580:     \"\"\"Deploy agent using AgentRuntime custom resource.\"\"\"\n581:     sanitized_name = self._sanitize_name(agent_name)\n582: \n583:     # Build AgentRuntime CR spec\n584:     agent_runtime = {\n585:         \"apiVersion\": \"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1\",\n586:         \"kind\": \"AgentRuntime\",\n587:         \"metadata\": {\n588:             \"name\": sanitized_name,\n589:             \"namespace\": self.namespace,\n590:         },\n591:         \"spec\": {\n592:             \"agentName\": agent_name,\n593:             \"image\": image_url,\n594:             \"port\": port,\n595:             \"entrypoint\": entrypoint or \"\",\n596:             \"env\": env_vars or {},\n597:             \"sessionTimeout\": \"15m\",\n598:             \"maxSessionDuration\": \"8h\",\n599:             \"imagePullSecrets\": [{\"name\": \"default-secret\"}],\n\n(Showing lines 200-599 of 1657. Use offset=600 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"                provider=provider,\n                node_port=node_port,\n                replicas=replicas,\n                namespace=namespace,\n                progress=progress,\n            )\n\n        console.print(\n            f\"[green]✓[/green] Agent published successfully\",\n            f\"  Metadata: {metadata_path}\",\n        )\n\n    except Exception as e:\n        _handle_error(e, \"publish\", verbose)\n```\n\n**Key Features**:\n- Comprehensive option set for all publishing scenarios\n- Rich progress tracking with multiple tasks\n- Provider selection (agentcube/k8s)","truncated":true,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-022/design.md","time":{"start":1775867850391,"end":1775867850408}}}}
