hon)\n1538: - [AgentRuntime CRD Specification](./deployment/client-go.md)\n1539: - [Rich Documentation](https://rich.readthedocs.io/)\n1540: \n1541: ## Appendix A: Complete Command Reference\n1542: \n1543: ### publish Command Options\n1544: \n1545: | Option | Type | Default | Description |\n1546: |--------|------|---------|-------------|\n1547: | `--workspace`, `-f` | string | `.` | Path to the agent workspace directory |\n1548: | `--version` | string | `None` | Semantic version string (e.g., v1.0.0) |\n1549: | `--image-url` | string | `None` | Image repository URL (required in local build mode) |\n1550: | `--image-username` | string | `None` | Username for image repository |\n1551: | `--image-password` | string | `None` | Password for image repository |\n1552: | `--description` | string | `None` | Agent description |\n1553: | `--region` | string | `None` | Deployment region |\n1554: | `--cloud-provider` | string | `None` | Cloud provider name (e.g., huawei) |\n1555: | `--provider` | string | `agentcube` | Target provider: 'agentcube' or 'k8s' |\n1556: | `--node-port` | int | `None` | Specific NodePort to use (30000-32767) |\n1557: | `--replicas` | int | `None` | Number of replicas for K8s deployment (default: 1) |\n1558: | `--namespace` | string | `None` | The namespace for the deployment |\n1559: | `--verbose` | bool | `False` | Enable detailed logging |\n1560: \n1561: ## Appendix B: Example Workflows\n1562: \n1563: ### Example 1: Publish to AgentCube with Local Image\n1564: \n1565: ```bash\n1566: # Build the agent\n1567: kubectl-agentcube build -f /path/to/agent\n1568: \n1569: # Publish to AgentCube\n1570: kubectl-agentcube publish \\\n1571:   --workspace /path/to/agent \\\n1572:   --image-url registry.example.com/my-agent:v1.0.0 \\\n1573:   --image-username myuser \\\n1574:   --image-password mypass \\\n1575:   --provider agentcube \\\n1576:   --version v1.0.0\n1577: ```\n1578: \n1579: ### Example 2: Publish to Kubernetes with Custom NodePort\n1580: \n1581: ```bash\n1582: kubectl-agentcube publish \\\n1583:   --workspace /path/to/agent \\\n1584:   --provider k8s \\\n1585:   --namespace production \\\n1586:   --replicas 3 \\\n1587:   --node-port 30080\n1588: ```\n1589: \n1590: ### Example 3: Publish with Environment Variables\n1591: \n1592: ```bash\n1593: export DOCKER_REGISTRY_URL=registry.example.com\n1594: export DOCKER_REGISTRY_USERNAME=myuser\n1595: export DOCKER_REGISTRY_PASSWORD=mypass\n1596: \n1597: kubectl-agentcube publish \\\n1598:   --workspace /path/to/agent \\\n1599:   --provider agentcube\n\n(Showing lines 1500-1599 of 1657. Use offset=1600 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"- Implement `PublishRuntime` class\n- Implement local image preparation\n- Implement AgentCube provider deployment\n- Unit tests for core functionality\n\n### Phase 2: Kubernetes Provider (Week 2)\n\n- Implement Kubernetes provider deployment\n- Implement readiness waiting\n- Implement error handling\n- Integration tests for K8s provider\n\n### Phase 3: Registry Integration (Week 3)\n\n- Implement Docker SDK integration\n- Implement registry authentication\n- Implement error handling for registry operations\n- Tests for various registry scenarios\n\n### Phase 4: Cloud Provider Support (Week 4)","truncated":true,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-022/design.md","time":{"start":1775867859421,"end":1775867859444}}}}
